  "prob_desc_output_spec": "Print w — the required minimal number of digits to erase. After removing the appropriate w digits from the number n, the result should have a value that is divisible by 10k. The result can start with digit 0 in the single case (the result is zero and written by exactly the only digit 0).",
  "source_code": "#include <stdio.h>\nint main()\n{\n    int di[10],n,n1,k,digit,count0,count;\n    for(count0=0;count0<10;count0++) di[count0]=0;\n    digit=1;\n    count=count0=0;\n    scanf(\"%d %d\",&n,&k);\n    n1=n;\n    while(n1!=n1%10&&count0<k)\n    {\n        di[digit-1]=n1%10;\n        digit++;\n        if(n1%10==0) count0++;\n        if(n1%10!=0) count++;\n        n1=n1/10;\n    }\n    if(n==0) printf(\"%d\",0);\n    else if(k==count0) printf(\"%d\",count);\n    else if(count0<k&&count0==0) printf(\"%d\",digit);\n    else printf(\"%d\",digit-1);\n}\n",
